"If you omit both the `locations` and the `value` attributes from the "
"`@ContextConfiguration` annotation, the TestContext framework tries to "
"detect a default XML resource location. Specifically, "
"`GenericXmlContextLoader` and `GenericXmlWebContextLoader` detect a default "
"location based on the name of the test class. If your class is named "
"`com.example.MyTest`, `GenericXmlContextLoader` loads your application "
"context from `\"classpath:com/example/MyTest-context.xml\"`. The following "
"example shows how to do so:"
msgstr ""

